The article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama declaring April 20, 2010, as National Equal Pay Day. The proclamation highlights the ongoing issue of pay inequity for women in the United States and the efforts being made to address this issue. Obama mentions the Lilly Ledbetter Fair Pay Restoration Act, the White House Council on Women and Girls, the National Equal Pay Enforcement Task Force, and the Office for Global Women's Issues as initiatives aimed at achieving wage fairness and eliminating barriers for women in the workforce. The proclamation calls on all Americans to acknowledge the injustice of wage discrimination and support efforts to achieve equal pay for equal work.